│ defined mask elements are within the expected range for two-source shuffles\n │
│ // based on the provided operand element count. This guards predicates that   │
│ assume\n  // per-operand element counts from out-of-bounds indices.\n  for    │
│ (int I : Mask) {\n    if (I == -1)\n      continue;\n    if (I < 0 || I >=    │
│ (NumSrcElts * 2))\n      return false;\n  }\n  // Select is differentiated    │
│ from identity. It requires using both sources.\n  if                          │
│ (isSingleSourceMask(Mask, NumSrcElts))\n    return false;\n  for (int I = 0,  │
│ E = Mask.size(); I < E; ++I) {\n    if (Mask[I] == -1)\n      continue;\n     │
│ if (Mask[I] != I && Mask[I] != (NumSrcElts + I))\n      return false;\n  }\n  │
